'resample' method for SplitCV objects

Source: R/Resampling.R
resample.Rd

method that creates a ResamplePrediction. It contain the relevant result information of a resampling: the predictions made, the relevant ground truth values, and possibly the training tasks and trained model for each fold

resample(data, inducer, split_cv)

Arguments

data

A Dataset object

inducer

An Inducer Object

split_cv

The split method

Examples

cars.data <- Dataset(data = cars, target = "dist")
xgb <- InducerConstructer(configuration = list(nrounds = 10, verbose = 0), method = "XGBoost")
cars.split <- splt$cv(folds = 5)(cars.data)
resample(cars.data, xgb, cars.split)
